init_text:
Once upon a time there was an old mother pig who had one hundred little pigs and not enough food to feed them. So when they were old enough, she sent them out into the world to seek their fortunes. You know the story about the first three little pigs. This is a story about the 92nd little pig.

The 92nd little pig built a house out of depleted uranium. And the wolf was like, "dude."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The wolf was very angry and he said, "I am going to blow down your house with my huffing and puffing."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The wolf was very angry and said, "I will blow you down with my dynamite."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: and thought about what he could do.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He thought and thought and then he had an idea.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He went to the store and bought a can of gasoline and a box of matches.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: So he went to the pig's house and poured the gasoline all over the house and then lit a match and threw it on the house.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The house caught on fire and burned down to the ground.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The wolf was happy and went to town to tell everyone how he had burned down the house and the pig.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The wolf was very proud of himself and he went to the bar and got drunk.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The next day the wolf went to the pig's house and the pig was sitting on the ground crying.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The wolf said, "I am sorry I burned your house down, I will make it up to you."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The wolf said, "I will build you a new house."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The pig said, "okay, but what kind of house will you build me?"

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The wolf said, "I will build you a house made from bricks."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The pig said, "okay, but what kind of bricks will you use?"

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The wolf said, "I will use the best bricks there are, the ones made from gold."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The pig said, "okay, but what kind of gold will you use?"

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The wolf said, "I will use the best gold there is, the kind that is mined from the ground."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The pig said, "okay, but what kind of ground will you mine it from?"

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The wolf said, "I will mine it from the ground that is made from uranium."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: So the wolf and the pig went to the uranium mine and the wolf started to mine the uranium and the pig started to build his house.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The wolf was very happy because he knew the pig was going to have a great house and he was going to get the uranium that he wanted.
